		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's a great overview, thanks! Might help someone come to conclusions to up their game next year, + could serve as a discussion basis for future compos (you seemed to be looking for one in the podcast interview?)<br /><br />I was more thinking that each game submission is a sheet, y is judgement category and x is all the marks that merit got sorted lowest to highest. This keeps the anonymity of the entrants/judges but gives all the data. <br /><br />I was first thinking about the raw judgement entries, but even with the names crossed out they wouldn't be anonymous because of giving oneself top marks.

		

